#ubuntu on chat.freenode.net
~/.gconf
~/ is automatically expanded to equal /home/USERNAME/
just /home/username
you're welcome
btw, I think your ! key might be feeling a bit sore
or nautilus & disown
don't do that as root
what are you trying to do in response to that?
don't do it from the system monitor
use ps ax | grep nautilus, find the PID of nautilus run by root, then use sudo kill PID
replace ax with aux
the PID is the number after the username
it should regardless of the kernel version
the versions in the update manager are slightly different than what the linux kernel's developers make
